* An-Nusub were stone-altars at fixed places or graves, whereon sacrifices were slaughtered on certain occasions in the name of idols, jinn, angels, pious men, saints in order to honour them, or to expect some benefit from them.,footnotes:2:[{5:90} What is said regarding the one who regards an alcoholic drink lawful to drink, and calls it by another name.]
