  6,49,"But those who reject Our Ayât (proofs, evidence, verses, lessons, signs, revelations, etc.), the torment will touch them for their disbelief{1} (and for their belying the Message of Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم). [Tafsir Al-Qurtubî].",footnotes:1:[{6:49} See the footnote of {3:85}.]
  6,50,"Say (O Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم): "
  6,51,"And warn therewith (the Qur’ân) those who fear that they will be gathered before their Lord, when there will be neither a protector nor an intercessor for them besides Him, so that they may fear Allâh and keep their duty to Him (by abstaining from committing sins and by doing all kinds of good deeds which He has ordained)."
